 <entry>
   <title>Clank - Beginnings</title>
   <link href="http://getclank.com/2013/06/05/clank-beginnings.html"/>
   <updated>2013-06-05T00:00:00+02:00</updated>
   <id>http://getclank.com/2013/06/05/clank-beginnings</id>
   <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;
  &lt;img class='alignright' height='300' src='http://getclank.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/screen-shot-2013-06-05-at-19-51-38.png?w=179&amp;amp;h=300' width='179' /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is the blog for the &lt;a href='https://github.com/Wolfr/clank'&gt;Clank&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;open source project.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You might be wondering: WTF is Clank?&amp;nbsp;Clank is an open source HTML/CSS framework for prototyping native apps. It’s a set of components that will help you communicate your design.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In theory you could use Clank to make a real app – but I wouldn’t recommend it. Browser support is minimal as Clank is used to convey the idea of an app to app developers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I am looking for contributors to help with the actual website, documentation and testing the framework. Get in &lt;a href='http://wolfslittlestore.be/contact/'&gt;touch&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
 </entry>
 
